## Next up

### Post-upload back-ref investigation [next task]

`ingest/tests/post_upload.test.ts:93` is currently `it.skip`-ed:

```ts
it.skip("papyri.examples:example1 has papyri.examples as a back-reference", ...)
```

The assertion checks that `papyri.examples` (the module) shows up in
the back-ref set of `papyri.examples:example1` (a function defined in
that module). The premise is sound: the module docstring (`papyri/
examples.py:227`) contains `:func:`example1``, which gen turns into a
CrossRef forward-link from `papyri.examples` → `papyri.examples:example1`.
The TypeScript ingester is supposed to record an edge for that, so
back-refs from `example1` should include `papyri.examples`. They do
not.

Surfaced when the `python-package.yml` YAML bug (commit `f9f7837`)
was fixed and `upload-verify` ran for the first time. Since the YAML
was silently rejected by GHA from the moment the test was added
(commit `547e4ee`), this assertion has never been validated in CI.

Likely candidates (TS ingester):

1. `ingest/src/visitor.ts:collectForwardRefs` may not walk into
   module-level CrossRefs the way the Python `crosslink.py` walker
   does. Module docstrings end up partly in `_content` and partly in
   `arbitrary` — the walker has to cover both.
2. CrossRef relink: `CrossRef.reference` is the placeholder
   `RefInfo("current-module", "current-version", "to-resolve", name)`.
   Whoever resolves that to the real `(papyri, <ver>, module,
   "papyri.examples:example1")` may be missing for module-level
   sources.
3. Mismatched key shape: Python `Key.path`, TS schema column
   `identifier`. The test reads `k.path`; if `getBackRefs` returns
   rows shaped `{package, version, category, identifier}` rather
   than `{module, version, kind, path}`, the filter
   `(k) => k.path === "papyri.examples"` is always-falsy.

Once the ingester is fixed (or the test re-shaped), drop the
`it.skip(` and the `TODO(ingest-backref):` comment in
`ingest/tests/post_upload.test.ts`.



